307
00:32:22.519 --> 00:32:29.519
He's had a horrible starting place being the Holidays Act and so many things to to address and it does.

308
00:32:29.519 --> 00:32:35.519
From my point of view really I really sense some positive development moving ahead from the Holidays Act.

309
00:32:35.519 --> 00:32:45.519
And a very clear attempt to address a wide range of issues things like casual staff and the pro-ratering of sick leave from day one, dealing with on call and stuff like that.

310
00:32:45.519 --> 00:32:48.519
Yeah, raise my hat to you all.

311
00:32:48.519 --> 00:32:54.519
And especially as you now try and process everything that's coming at you in this consultation.

312
00:32:54.519 --> 00:32:57.519
Now I speak on behalf of SMEs.

313
00:32:57.519 --> 00:33:01.519
I have some 400 or 500 whom I provided HR advice to.

314
00:33:01.519 --> 00:33:10.519
And I've been pleased that I can already go back to them and confirm for many of them that their concerns will be addressed in the new legislation.

315
00:33:10.519 --> 00:33:13.519
And there'll always be some of course that are not.

316
00:33:13.519 --> 00:33:22.519
There is one though in particular, and it's the first and significant issue that I referred to in my written submission that I want to address today.

317
00:33:22.519 --> 00:33:28.519
And I strongly suggest you consider the particular recommendation that I'm going to make.

318
00:33:28.519 --> 00:33:36.519
And the reality is that this is all about enabling small businesses to comply with the legislation.

319
00:33:36.519 --> 00:33:45.519
So I want you to start by picturing an SME, maybe a small retail outlet, a cafe, a restaurant, a roofing contractor.

320
00:33:45.519 --> 00:33:54.519
There are any number of them whose workload is dependent on the weather or on a daily varying level of customer demand.

321
00:33:54.519 --> 00:34:01.519
We all know them and these businesses can thrive, but that's especially where staff are working as a team.

322
00:34:01.519 --> 00:34:07.519
They dig deep sometimes. They leave early where that benefits the business.

323
00:34:07.519 --> 00:34:10.519
They'll work a Saturday to help make up time.

324
00:34:10.519 --> 00:34:15.519
And for these and many others, compliance with the holidays act was just a nightmare.

325
00:34:15.519 --> 00:34:19.519
There was no way a business owner could understand what was needed to comply.

326
00:34:19.519 --> 00:34:24.519
So they relied on their payroll provider to do things right.

327
00:34:24.519 --> 00:34:30.519
But we all know that at some stage, all payroll systems were non-compliant with the holidays act.

328
00:34:30.519 --> 00:34:41.519
And yet it was the SME who bore the brunt and the cost of a labor inspector's audit and its resulting penalties.

329
00:34:41.519 --> 00:34:44.519
And it just didn't seem right.

330
00:34:44.519 --> 00:35:04.519
For example, how many payroll systems that you know do you think would cope easily with a roster that has somebody working Wednesday, seven hours, Thursday, 10, Friday, 10, Saturday, 14 and a half, Sunday, two, with sleepovers in between each of them, then three days rest and then going through the whole thing again.

331
00:35:04.519 --> 00:35:13.519
It was a roster that effectively is an eight-day revolving roster, but payroll systems just couldn't cope with it.

332
00:35:13.519 --> 00:35:18.519
It was almost not possible to comply with the legislation.

333
00:35:18.519 --> 00:35:29.519
We need something similar, something simple, rather not similar, something simple to manage what have become some of the most complex of rosters.

334
00:35:29.519 --> 00:35:37.519
And while this bill has gone so far, it can easily go a step further in removing complexity.

335
00:35:37.519 --> 00:35:42.519
It's a real challenge when it comes to drafting legislation, I know.

336
00:35:42.519 --> 00:35:57.519
And I just pulled out section one, two, three of the bill, section two, subsection two, where the employee's leave payment must not be less than the rate of leave payment for each relevant hour that the employee takes as a period of leave,

337
00:35:57.519 --> 00:36:03.519
or that he does not work on a public holiday that would otherwise be a working day, et cetera, et cetera.

338
00:36:03.519 --> 00:36:12.519
For most business owners, if you present them with that, it's not that it's wrong, it's not, it's correct.

339
00:36:12.519 --> 00:36:21.519
But it's just that it leaves them saying, the business owners are never going to get their heads around it.

340
00:36:21.519 --> 00:36:27.519
For the SMEs that I had you picturing before, there's no simple standard hours.

341
00:36:27.519 --> 00:36:38.519
And the many additional hours may or may not be linked to an availability clause, because for many of them it's actually just part of their commitment to their jobs.

342
00:36:39.519 --> 00:36:51.519
So we need a simpler way to collect dollars for leave payments broadly, and for ease of understanding and to avoid having to rely on the payroll provider for compliance.

343
00:36:51.519 --> 00:36:58.519
So please, can we have just a few very simple rules built into this legislation?

344
00:36:58.519 --> 00:37:11.519
The first one, for every dollar that you earn, you put aside or that somebody earns, you put aside another 12.5 cents for leave, 8.5 probably for annual leave, 4 for sick leave.

345
00:37:11.519 --> 00:37:18.519
For every hour worked, you accrue the 0.0769 hours plus 0.0385 hours.

346
00:37:18.519 --> 00:37:24.519
For every uncertain otherwise working day, we use the 13 weeks.

347
00:37:24.519 --> 00:37:29.519
It is great. You've got some very simple stuff already built into the draft legislation.

348
00:37:29.519 --> 00:37:34.519
Take it that step further that all earnings get treated the same way.

349
00:37:34.519 --> 00:37:38.519
You don't separate out standard hours from other hours.

350
00:37:38.519 --> 00:37:47.519
That everything that relates to hours worked or protection of employment or employment status, leave that with the Employment Relations Act.

351
00:37:47.519 --> 00:37:53.519
We don't need to muddy the waters within the Employment Leave Act.

352
00:37:53.519 --> 00:38:00.519
And leave it so that payroll providers are doing just that. They're providing a payroll service.

353
00:38:00.519 --> 00:38:17.519
I really urge you to press on. Don't allow the tightness of the timeframe to stop you from making that extra change and making it that little bit more simple that employers will be able to comply.

354
00:38:17.519 --> 00:38:19.519
Are there any questions?

