00:47:33.519 --> 00:47:36.519
so I'm just trying to think of a scenario

479
00:47:36.519 --> 00:47:38.519
where you would work outside of a roster.

480
00:47:38.519 --> 00:47:41.519
Have you got a scenario where you'd be work,

481
00:47:41.519 --> 00:47:44.519
there would be work outside of the roster?

482
00:47:44.519 --> 00:47:48.519
There's quite often situations, I'll use a manufacturing example

483
00:47:48.519 --> 00:47:52.519
because I've had that kind of experience where people have a standard roster

484
00:47:52.519 --> 00:47:54.519
that their shift roster if you like,

485
00:47:54.519 --> 00:47:58.519
but then there are times when, for instance,

486
00:47:58.519 --> 00:48:01.519
the mill is shut down for maintenance

487
00:48:01.519 --> 00:48:03.519
and that roster is still working,

488
00:48:03.519 --> 00:48:06.519
but then there's a whole lot of other extra work to be done for maintenance

489
00:48:06.519 --> 00:48:09.519
so that people agree that they will add another four or five hours

490
00:48:09.519 --> 00:48:15.519
